- Add lib/local-nlp-waiter.js: zero-dependency, rule-based intent engine
  covering greetings, menu, recommendations, add items (qty-aware),
  allergies, spice level, wants/avoids, notes, place order, payment,
  cart/total, small talk, FAQ, and varied fallbacks. Never throws.

- Rewire app/api/[[...path]]/route.js to use the local engine in both
  demo-mode and supabase-backed code paths. Remove the 'brain freeze'
  fallback entirely — it was the visible symptom of missing/broken
  OpenRouter/Groq keys on Vercel.

- Add tests/test_local_nlp_waiter.mjs: 33 deterministic scenario tests,
  all passing (intents, qty extraction, avoid/want parsing, fallbacks).

No external API calls; works offline, on Vercel Edge, or anywhere Node runs.
